The paper presents two stable mergesort variants that optimize merging orders and are competitive with state-of-the-art sorting methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Algorithm (cs.AL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of merging orders, which is related to combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) due to its focus on optimizing sorting methods.
